reviewText: Put together Jeff Foxworthy, Bill Engvall and Larry the Cable Guy and you have a riotous evening of fun.  We enjoyed this latest in the Blue Collar series.
Title: Them Idiots: Whirled Tour

reviewText: These comedians are all so down to earth, and genuinely hilarious with the smallest topic you can think of, and make people laugh 'til their sides split.  My laughter, tears of enjoyment, and applause go to these 3 nutcases, plus Ron White.  The world is a better place with these funny characters!
summary: I haven't watched this yet, but I'm sure looking forward to laughing at them
Title: Them Idiots: Whirled Tour

reviewText: This was very  hilarious. Both a gift for me and my father. We were laughing our asses off completely. These idiots sure know their jokes in the comedy world or reality. They even talked about colonoscopies. hehe. And farting to.
summary: Best video to get for your kids and family. I highly recommend it to anyone in the USA.
Title: Them Idiots: Whirled Tour

reviewText: These guys are always hilarious and my favorites are Bill and Jeff.  I have several of their dvds and they are just to funny!

reviewText: When these three get together, there are no limits on conversational topics or crazy thoughts. Best medicine for the blues.
Title: Them Idiots: Whirled Tour

reviewerName: Don't tread on me "Defending the Conservative...
reviewText: It is good to see these guys back together.  Not being a fan of Ron White, I didn't miss him.  Jeff and Bill are absolutely great.  However, what happened to Larry?  He has gotten a lot cruder (similar to Ron White).  His jokes were not that funny, and the crowd doesn't laugh nearly as much.  I am undecided if I want to buy the DVD for just Bill and Jeff.
Title: Them Idiots: Whirled Tour

reviewText: If you want to laugh big and look at the human condition at the same time, this is for you. These guys are polished and gifted comedians - don't let the Country-Schtick fool you. Larry is a bit rough around the edges, but funny. Engvaal is my favorite.
summary: Very funny, but for Adults and older teens.
Title: Them Idiots: Whirled Tour

reviewText: absolutely hysterical! i love these guys and im glad to see them do another show. i like ron white, but i think the show without him is a lot cleaner.

reviewText: About what you would expect from this bunch of nuts :)  Another solid performance but probably on the lower end as far as their other DVDs.  Audio and video is both good.
Title: Them Idiots: Whirled Tour

reviewText: This is hilarious, as expected -- I'd say it's not as good as the Blue Collar Comedy Tour videos, but it can hold it's own.  I expected a little more "funny" from Bill Engvall -- and as usual, Jeff Foxworthy stole the show -- I was literally rolling on the floor laughing his routine was that funny.  If Bill had had a better routine, I'd have given it a "5" -- Larry the Cable Guy was his usual funny self -- but I'm not always impressed with his humor...
Title: Them Idiots: Whirled Tour

reviewText: Without Ron White it just not the same. He really did not fit in with the others type of comedy and the fans they attracted. Dont get me wrong i really liked their Red Neck Comedy shows (all 3 of them). But its time to move on like Ron did.
Title: Them Idiots: Whirled Tour

reviewText: Ron White is missing from this line up. It make it a bit different. They have a "host" named Reno that does a minor routine - he still needs polish.  Bill, Jeff and Larry are more family oriented than ever - and it is appreciated. Hard to not like Them Idiots. Sorry Ron, you are missed, but not sorely......
Title: Them Idiots: Whirled Tour

reviewText: These guys are a riot. all you will do is laugh and laugh and laugh and laugh til you hurt.
